# Agent Division

- Development environment is `Cursor + Claude Code`, and Cursor-side implementation uses GPT-5.4.
- Cursor GPT-5.4 should lead:
  - React and Next.js UI in `app/**/*.tsx` and `components/**/*.tsx`
  - shadcn/ui composition and Tailwind styling
  - small single-file improvements and UI-focused docs updates
- Claude Code should lead:
  - DB schema and `supabase/migrations/**`
  - RLS, auth, tenant isolation, and role design
  - `app/api/**`, `lib/server/**`, and multi-file architecture changes
- If a task crosses both areas, split it explicitly:
  - Claude Code defines schema, API, auth, and server contracts
  - Cursor implements screens and client interaction on top of those contracts
- Do not let Cursor-side work silently decide backend policy.

## Restricted Files (Do Not Touch)
- `middleware.ts` — Next.js middleware. Must be named exactly `middleware.ts` with the exported function named `middleware`. Renaming to `proxy.ts` or any other name breaks authentication. Claude Code owns this file.
